cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning framework for macro action selection in StarCraft, which involves multi-agent collaboration and hidden information. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also discusses the game theory aspect of the problem, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.GT (Game Theory). The use of LSTM in the proposed framework also indicates the relevance to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
